2006-07-23 11:23  chris_kohlhoff

	* boostify.pl, src/doc/examples_dox.txt,
	  src/doc/boost/examples_dox.txt, src/examples/timers/Jamfile: Add
	  timers examples to documentation, and include them in boost
	  layout package.

2006-07-22 10:10  chris_kohlhoff

	* include/asio/ssl/detail/openssl_stream_service.hpp: Missed
	  passing recv_buf to one openssl_operation constructor call.

2006-07-22 09:04  chris_kohlhoff

	* include/asio/ssl/detail/: openssl_operation.hpp,
	  openssl_stream_service.hpp: Fix two problems in the SSL
	  implementation:

	  - A read operation should check the read buffer first to see if
	  there's any	data present and use that first, before issuing a
	  new read from the   socket.

	  - The read buffer was a member of the openssl_operation class,
	  and a new   openssl_operation object is created for each read or
	  write initiated by   the application. This meant that any surplus
	  data from a previous read is	 lost. Changed the buffer to be a
	  member of the stream object.

2006-07-20 08:39  chris_kohlhoff

	* src/examples/timers/time_t_timer.cpp: Don't wrap the time_t time
	  value in a class, just the duration.

2006-07-20 00:42  chris_kohlhoff

	* src/: Makefile.bor, Makefile.mgw, Makefile.msc,
	  examples/timers/tick_count_timer.cpp,
	  examples/timers/time_t_timer.cpp: Add example illustrating a
	  custom timer using GetTickCount().

2006-07-19 23:22  chris_kohlhoff

	* include/Makefile.am, include/asio/deadline_timer_service.hpp,
	  include/asio/time_traits.hpp,
	  include/asio/detail/deadline_timer_service.hpp,
	  include/asio/detail/epoll_reactor.hpp,
	  include/asio/detail/kqueue_reactor.hpp,
	  include/asio/detail/reactive_deadline_timer_service.hpp,
	  include/asio/detail/reactor_timer_queue.hpp,
	  include/asio/detail/select_reactor.hpp,
	  include/asio/detail/timer_queue.hpp,
	  include/asio/detail/timer_queue_base.hpp, src/Makefile.am,
	  src/examples/timers/.cvsignore,
	  src/examples/timers/time_t_timer.cpp: Maintain separate timer
	  queues for each time traits type. This is necessary to support a
	  monotonic timer that is not affected by changes to the system
	  clock.

